Gluster 3.2: Checking Geo-replication Minimum Requirements[Checking
Geo-replication Minimum Requirements>>]

Deploying Gluster Geo-replication involves the following steps:

1.  Verify that GlusterFS v3.2 is installed and running on systems that
will serve as masters, using the following command: +
 +
#glusterfs --version
2.  Verify that your environment matches the minimum system
requirements. For more information, see
Gluster 3.2: Checking Geo-replication Minimum Requirements[ Checking
Geo-replication Minimum Requirements].
3.  Determine the appropriate deployment scenario. For more information,
see Gluster 3.2: Exploring Geo-replication Deployment Scenarios[
Exploring Geo-replication Deployment Scenarios].
4.  Start Gluster Geo-replication on master and slave systems, as
required. For more information, see
Gluster 3.2: Starting Gluster Geo-replication[ Starting Gluster
Geo-replication].

